The SRxCryptoAPI requires the following software packages installed:

openssl and openssl-devel
libconfig

To compile the api the following switches allow customization

--enable-bgpsec-openssl
      This switch includes the BGPSEC open-ssl implementation to be added.

--enable-testlib
      Enable the compilation of the test library. This library only provides 
      the plug in skeleton.

For customized OpenSSL installations use:
openssl_dir="<path to customized openssl installation>"


./configure --prefix=<install-direcotry> CFLAGS="-g -O0" --enable-bgpsec-openssl --enable-testlib
